(Adapted from iceread.com novel
"You Xi" by Qingyang Wanxi)

3
00:01:15,220 --> 00:01:17,700
=Episode 7=

4
00:01:24,649 --> 00:01:25,330
Excuse me.

5
00:01:25,849 --> 00:01:27,330
Is Dr. Li here?

6
00:01:27,690 --> 00:01:28,409
Yes, he is.

7
00:01:28,970 --> 00:01:30,369
He's in Exam Room 8, right?

8
00:01:30,369 --> 00:01:30,890
Yes.

9
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:31,810
Thank you.

10
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:38,120
Please come in.

11
00:01:38,810 --> 00:01:39,569
Dr. Li,

12
00:01:39,648 --> 00:01:40,810
I hope I'm not disturbing you.

13
00:01:41,610 --> 00:01:42,649
No. Come in.

14
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:50,289
You're eating this for lunch?

15
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:53,009
I was busy. I didn't have time
to go down for lunch.

16
00:01:53,409 --> 00:01:54,489
Just grabbing a bite.

17
00:01:54,849 --> 00:01:56,649
You can't eat spicy sticks for lunch.

18
00:01:58,769 --> 00:01:59,690
Have this.

19
00:01:59,929 --> 00:02:01,730
My mom packed me a work meal.

20
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:03,610
I was supposed to be back at the office,

21
00:02:03,610 --> 00:02:05,489
but my superior
made me go home and rest.

22
00:02:05,849 --> 00:02:07,530
I'll eat when I get home.

23
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:09,249
What kind of great leader is that?

24
00:02:10,209 --> 00:02:11,290
Well, I'll take it.

25
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:12,089
Go ahead.

26
00:02:14,769 --> 00:02:17,369
I thought your follow-up was next week.

27
00:02:18,130 --> 00:02:19,769
Yeah, next week.

28
00:02:19,769 --> 00:02:20,730
I came today to ask

29
00:02:20,730 --> 00:02:23,515
if you could write me a sick leave note
for interstitial pregnancy.

30
00:02:23,515 --> 00:02:25,093
My superior wants me to take sick leave.

31
00:02:25,137 --> 00:02:26,610
I'm afraid that if someone checks,

32
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:27,610
he'll get blamed.

33
00:02:27,969 --> 00:02:29,170
I see. I'll write it for you.

34
00:02:29,610 --> 00:02:30,209
Thank you.

35
00:02:37,489 --> 00:02:38,410
They're still warm.

36
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:39,529
Thank you.

37
00:02:44,893 --> 00:02:46,170
Give this to your company.

38
00:02:46,170 --> 00:02:47,730
Get it stamped at the triage desk.

39
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:49,950
The procedure is correct,
and it's good for your leader.

40
00:02:50,130 --> 00:02:51,489
You've got experience in this.

41
00:02:51,969 --> 00:02:52,610
Thank you.

42
00:02:52,689 --> 00:02:53,330
Li Jingzhe!

43
00:02:54,249 --> 00:02:54,969
Li Jingzhe!

44
00:02:54,969 --> 00:02:55,890
Come out!

45
00:02:56,249 --> 00:02:57,290
Come out, Li Jingzhe!

46
00:02:58,426 --> 00:02:59,760
He must be hiding in his office.

47
00:02:59,769 --> 00:03:00,440
Definitely here.

48
00:03:00,448 --> 00:03:01,670
Â­ Who's that?
- Li Jingzhe!

49
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,469
Li Jingzhe!

50
00:03:02,470 --> 00:03:03,050
Hospital brawl.

51
00:03:03,050 --> 00:03:04,640
I'll take you out through the back door.

52
00:03:04,689 --> 00:03:05,529
Li Jingzhe!

53
00:03:07,089 --> 00:03:08,369
There's a back door?

54
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,520
- This is a hospital.
- Don't touch me!

55
00:03:12,529 --> 00:03:13,450
Please calm down, madam.

56
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:14,890
- The nurse hits me!
- Get off me.

57
00:03:14,890 --> 00:03:15,850
Please calm down.

58
00:03:15,850 --> 00:03:16,369
Li Jingzhe!

59
00:03:16,369 --> 00:03:17,489
Please calm down, madam.

60
00:03:18,337 --> 00:03:19,570
- Where's he?
- Li Jingzhe!

61
00:03:21,182 --> 00:03:22,360
- Li Jingzhe!
- Li Jingzhe!

62
00:03:34,769 --> 00:03:35,570
Are you okay?

63
00:03:36,089 --> 00:03:37,969
Do you guys often run into this?

64
00:03:39,769 --> 00:03:40,570
Not quite.

65
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:42,330
Last month,

66
00:03:42,330 --> 00:03:44,010
a patient had a placental abruption.

67
00:03:44,330 --> 00:03:45,689
The baby didn't survive.

68
00:03:45,848 --> 00:03:47,026
The family couldn't accept it

69
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,890
and keeps coming back
to make trouble every few days.

70
00:03:48,893 --> 00:03:50,760
I'm one of the few male doctors
in the department,

71
00:03:50,769 --> 00:03:52,089
young and fast enough to run.

72
00:03:52,529 --> 00:03:54,969
So they sent me to handle it.

73
00:03:56,050 --> 00:03:56,850
I see.

74
00:03:58,089 --> 00:03:58,969
Are you really okay?

75
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:01,170
I'm good.

76
00:04:05,929 --> 00:04:08,529
Right now, I'm doing two things at once.

77
00:04:08,570 --> 00:04:09,610
Saving lives on one hand,

78
00:04:09,610 --> 00:04:11,290
and mapping out the hospital
on the other,

79
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:13,010
ready to escape anytime.

80
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:17,290
That hallway leads to the morgue.

81
00:04:17,290 --> 00:04:18,569
Nobody goes there.

82
00:04:18,569 --> 00:04:20,290
I was on the phone there that day.

83
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:21,610
Didn't expect to run into you.

84
00:04:23,449 --> 00:04:24,889
If it weren't for death stuff,

85
00:04:25,090 --> 00:04:26,329
I wouldn't have gone there.

86
00:04:27,689 --> 00:04:28,569
You know,

87
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:30,090
that day something occurred to me.

88
00:04:30,809 --> 00:04:33,449
If only my husband had cheated on me.

89
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,320
As long as he was still alive,

90
00:04:35,871 --> 00:04:37,210
everything else wouldn't matter.

91
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:44,249
What if

92
00:04:44,337 --> 00:04:45,515
he really cheats on you?

93
00:04:49,889 --> 00:04:50,650
I'd wish him well.

94
00:04:55,889 --> 00:04:57,610
That's typical for a mom-to-be.

95
00:04:57,689 --> 00:04:59,329
Your heart is
big enough to float a boat.

96
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:04,226
Hearts only get that big
because the boat pushes them open.

97
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:08,170
Every stroke hurts,

98
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,410
but you still have to keep rowing.

99
00:05:15,050 --> 00:05:16,410
Is it hard for you right now?

100
00:05:18,929 --> 00:05:19,689
It's okay.

101
00:05:21,650 --> 00:05:24,090
Do you have someone to talk to
when you're upset?

102
00:05:25,449 --> 00:05:26,210
No one.

103
00:05:35,689 --> 00:05:36,770
Someone dies.

104
00:05:38,329 --> 00:05:39,569
People die every day.

105
00:05:43,489 --> 00:05:45,170
So we have to live well,

106
00:05:45,889 --> 00:05:46,369
right?

107
00:05:48,689 --> 00:05:49,170
Yeah.

108
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:57,449
Blind dates? Oh, Mom.

109
00:05:57,970 --> 00:05:59,489
I'll find someone myself.

110
00:05:59,489 --> 00:06:00,569
Don't worry about it.

111
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:03,650
I promise you'll be satisfied, okay?

112
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:08,090
Fate can't be rushed.

113
00:06:09,249 --> 00:06:09,770
Oh my.

114
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:11,290
I'm hanging up.

115
00:06:14,530 --> 00:06:15,210
Hello.

116
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:16,493
What line is this?
[* "Line" sounds like "filling" in Mandarin]

117
00:06:18,129 --> 00:06:19,650
Pork and scallion. What's wrong?

118
00:06:20,929 --> 00:06:22,770
I'm asking, what line is this?

119
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:23,770
Solid line.

120
00:06:25,090 --> 00:06:26,249
I'm sorry.

121
00:06:26,249 --> 00:06:27,689
I'm sorry. I'll move right away.

122
00:06:29,129 --> 00:06:29,770
Mingzhu!

123
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:32,210
Hurry up. The traffic police are here.

124
00:06:35,889 --> 00:06:36,650
We're moving.

125
00:06:38,929 --> 00:06:39,569
Alright.

126
00:06:39,715 --> 00:06:40,730
I won't deduct points.

127
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:41,689
Just a 200 yuan fine.

128
00:06:42,249 --> 00:06:43,090
No, please.

129
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:44,650
My friend's pregnant.

130
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:45,489
She can't walk fast.

131
00:06:45,489 --> 00:06:46,770
Yes, I'm pregnant.

132
00:06:47,137 --> 00:06:48,480
Do you have an ultrasound photo?

133
00:06:48,489 --> 00:06:49,610
Show it to the officer.

134
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:50,689
It's real.

135
00:06:50,970 --> 00:06:52,569
She's pregnant.

136
00:06:53,730 --> 00:06:54,970
Alright. Move along.

137
00:06:54,970 --> 00:06:56,004
Okay. Thank you so much.

138
00:06:56,048 --> 00:06:56,982
Don't do it next time.

139
00:06:57,009 --> 00:06:58,689
Sure. Thank you, handsome officer.

140
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:10,679
Li Store's meat buns are amazing.

141
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,004
One bite and the juice bursts out.

142
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:15,410
You know what?
I ran into a hospital brawl just now.

143
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:16,569
It was scary.

144
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:18,009
Hospital brawls

145
00:07:18,009 --> 00:07:19,889
are meant to scare people.

146
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:21,009
If you get scared,

147
00:07:21,009 --> 00:07:22,249
they win.

148
00:07:22,449 --> 00:07:23,369
You should say this.

149
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:24,929
"Come on. Come at me.

150
00:07:24,929 --> 00:07:26,170
I'm pregnant.

151
00:07:26,170 --> 00:07:28,329
If you win, you'll support me
and the baby for life.

152
00:07:28,329 --> 00:07:30,040
If you lose, I'll support you for life."

153
00:07:30,048 --> 00:07:31,000
Then you win.

154
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,369
What would I do without you?

155
00:07:35,770 --> 00:07:37,170
Everyone can live without someone.

156
00:07:37,382 --> 00:07:39,050
You can live without Feng Jianqi too.

157
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:44,369
You don't have to remind me. I know.

158
00:07:46,129 --> 00:07:47,689
My birth parents gave me away,

159
00:07:47,689 --> 00:07:48,569
and I survived.

160
00:07:49,689 --> 00:07:51,050
So I'll survive anything.

161
00:09:23,969 --> 00:09:25,530
You've found your sister?

162
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:27,809
I'd say it's one-sided.

163
00:09:28,089 --> 00:09:29,609
We're not sure yet.

164
00:09:31,290 --> 00:09:32,809
I thought you were twins.

165
00:09:34,010 --> 00:09:35,490
You don't really look alike though.

166
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:37,530
Right? I don't think so either.

167
00:09:37,530 --> 00:09:38,648
But my parents think we do,

168
00:09:38,693 --> 00:09:39,490
especially my mom.

169
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:41,250
She's being dramatic.

170
00:09:41,650 --> 00:09:42,909
She can see all thirty years

171
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:44,250
of hardship the girl's been through

172
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,490
by reading her face.

173
00:09:45,849 --> 00:09:47,650
She wanted to rush over overnight.

174
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:48,929
If I were your mom

175
00:09:49,370 --> 00:09:50,170
and found out

176
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:51,449
I had another daughter at fifty,

177
00:09:51,449 --> 00:09:53,050
I'd rush over overnight too.

178
00:09:53,089 --> 00:09:54,170
I wouldn't wait a minute.

179
00:09:55,410 --> 00:09:56,410
I can understand.

180
00:09:58,170 --> 00:09:59,650
Why didn't my grandma

181
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:01,050
tell her earlier?

182
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:04,130
Zhidong,

183
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:06,920
if your grandma hadn't preferred boys
over girls,

184
00:10:07,089 --> 00:10:08,770
the one sent away might've been you.

185
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:11,050
That's possible.

186
00:10:11,804 --> 00:10:13,379
Let's go eat at Shen's Restaurant.

187
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,010
Take a look at
what your sister looks like.

188
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,290
See if she looks like you.

189
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:19,969
She's your biological sister.

190
00:10:20,329 --> 00:10:21,490
Aren't you curious?

191
00:10:22,290 --> 00:10:23,603
Even if she is,

192
00:10:23,604 --> 00:10:25,626
that doesn't mean
she wants to acknowledge me.

193
00:10:25,648 --> 00:10:27,130
I can't just show up like that.

194
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:28,650
They said online

195
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:29,609
she's pregnant.

196
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,569
That'd add to her pressure.

197
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:34,050
True.

198
00:10:53,370 --> 00:10:54,290
Your little bag.

199
00:10:55,209 --> 00:10:56,089
I'm heading home.

200
00:10:56,089 --> 00:10:56,849
Get home safe.

201
00:10:56,849 --> 00:10:57,890
Just leaving like this?

202
00:11:04,290 --> 00:11:04,890
Bye-bye.

203
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:05,969
Bye-bye.

204
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,840
(If your grandma
hadn't favored boys over girls,)

205
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:15,729
(the one sent away might've been you.)

206
00:11:16,089 --> 00:11:17,530
(She's your biological sister.)

207
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,170
(Aren't you curious?)

208
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:34,609
Dad, Mom, I'm home.

209
00:11:34,969 --> 00:11:35,650
Darling.

210
00:11:36,809 --> 00:11:39,209
Your dad bought your favorite durian.

211
00:11:39,604 --> 00:11:41,650
It's so expensive.
Only he would buy it for you.

212
00:11:42,689 --> 00:11:43,329
Dad.

213
00:11:43,849 --> 00:11:44,410
You're home.

214
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:45,410
Sit and try it.

215
00:11:45,969 --> 00:11:46,689
Eat some fruit.

216
00:11:47,582 --> 00:11:49,410
We're having dumplings
and wontons tonight.

217
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:50,449
You've wrapped so many.

218
00:11:51,609 --> 00:11:52,849
Did Zhidong send you home?

219
00:11:53,915 --> 00:11:55,680
You're going to get married
sooner or later.

220
00:11:55,849 --> 00:11:57,449
Both families will have to meet

221
00:11:57,449 --> 00:11:58,569
and talk.

222
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:00,530
What's the rush?

223
00:12:00,890 --> 00:12:01,729
The girl's side

224
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:04,290
shouldn't bring it up first.

225
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,449
Bichen's not worried
about finding a husband.

226
00:12:06,449 --> 00:12:07,130
Yeah.

227
00:12:07,609 --> 00:12:09,170
Says who?

228
00:12:09,370 --> 00:12:11,770
The Xu family is all busy
looking for their daughter now.

229
00:12:11,969 --> 00:12:13,370
They don't care about their son.

230
00:12:13,490 --> 00:12:14,370
They do care.

231
00:12:14,370 --> 00:12:15,770
One thing at a time.

232
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:16,770
I don't want to eat.

233
00:12:18,089 --> 00:12:20,490
The situation in Xu Zhidong's family
is too complicated.

234
00:12:20,809 --> 00:12:22,050
If I had known earlier,

235
00:12:22,290 --> 00:12:24,490
I would never have let Bichen date him.

236
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:34,410
(Shen Family Restaurant)

237
00:12:49,026 --> 00:12:50,050
What are you doing here?

238
00:12:51,426 --> 00:12:52,960
What are you doing in front of my house?

239
00:12:54,671 --> 00:12:56,440
I'm talking to you. Can't you hear me?

240
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,329
Who are you?

241
00:12:58,329 --> 00:12:59,130
Don't run!

242
00:13:00,337 --> 00:13:01,250
Sneaking photos again?

243
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:01,809
Who are you?

244
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:04,250
Talk! What are you doing here?

245
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:07,569
Hey.

246
00:13:07,826 --> 00:13:08,840
What's wrong with you?

247
00:13:09,089 --> 00:13:10,010
Who are you?

248
00:13:10,809 --> 00:13:11,729
Who the heck are you?

249
00:13:11,729 --> 00:13:12,650
Sneaking photos again?

250
00:13:14,209 --> 00:13:14,770
Let go.

251
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:16,130
You're hitting me?

252
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,370
Here. Your ID cards.

253
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:32,969
Thank you.

254
00:13:34,260 --> 00:13:35,849
(Xu Zhidong, March 26, 1994)

255
00:13:35,849 --> 00:13:36,609
This is yours.

256
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:39,530
You have the same birthday as my sister.

257
00:13:47,329 --> 00:13:48,089
From Nanzhou?

258
00:13:50,569 --> 00:13:51,449
Which part of Nanzhou?

259
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:54,449
Why did you try to run away?

260
00:13:55,890 --> 00:13:56,770
Who are your parents?

261
00:13:57,370 --> 00:13:58,609
Where's your hometown?

262
00:13:58,770 --> 00:13:59,929
Why are you asking so much?

263
00:14:00,929 --> 00:14:02,209
You don't get to ask.

264
00:14:03,729 --> 00:14:04,929
Who's coming for you?

265
00:14:04,937 --> 00:14:06,115
- My sister.
- My sister.

266
00:14:09,050 --> 00:14:09,890
Where is he?

267
00:14:11,170 --> 00:14:12,890
Ask them.

268
00:14:12,890 --> 00:14:13,689
Officer.

269
00:14:13,689 --> 00:14:14,929
- Get in line.
- I'm Xu...

270
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,010
There's a queue here.

271
00:14:17,089 --> 00:14:17,729
Line up.

272
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:22,469
Where's Zhidong? Is he all right?

273
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:24,760
Don't worry, Mom.
Zhidong was the one who got beaten.

274
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,250
We're in the right here. Don't worry.

275
00:14:26,982 --> 00:14:28,800
Someone from your family caused trouble?

276
00:14:29,130 --> 00:14:30,849
No. It's not that.

277
00:14:31,089 --> 00:14:32,849
We were the ones who got attacked.

278
00:14:32,849 --> 00:14:34,329
We're the victims.

279
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:37,770
Was it two young guys fighting?

280
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:38,809
With Hui.

281
00:14:39,370 --> 00:14:40,809
Hui?

282
00:14:40,969 --> 00:14:41,969
You don't know him?

283
00:14:41,969 --> 00:14:42,849
No.

284
00:14:43,849 --> 00:14:45,890
That brat is trouble.

285
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:48,199
He spent five years in high school
and still didn't graduate.

286
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,560
Everyone in the neighborhood
has suffered because of him.

287
00:14:50,737 --> 00:14:52,530
He even went after
his own brother-in-law.

288
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:53,929
He stuck this huge snake

289
00:14:53,929 --> 00:14:55,650
into his brother-in-law's pants.

290
00:14:56,609 --> 00:14:57,209
What...

291
00:14:57,890 --> 00:14:59,729
What happened to the brother-in-law?

292
00:14:59,729 --> 00:15:00,530
He died.

293
00:15:06,929 --> 00:15:08,809
Your brother's an honest lad,

294
00:15:08,809 --> 00:15:10,530
and now he's caught up with that brat.

295
00:15:10,729 --> 00:15:12,969
We're in real trouble.

296
00:15:12,969 --> 00:15:13,689
It's okay, Mom.

297
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,010
I'm here.

298
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,990
Have the families
of Xu Zhidong and Shen Minghui arrived?

299
00:15:19,004 --> 00:15:19,737
Yes.

300
00:15:21,370 --> 00:15:22,370
Come with me.

301
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:26,250
